We now have clear clusters for the eyes, mouth, and "other". For some videos, there are two eye clusters (one for each eye), but for others there is only one (for both eyes). This is fine because fixation points in the eye region will generally be assigned to simply "eyes".

```{r, fig.width=15, fig.height=15}
